Dear Manus,

Remember me? I believe I promised you a Pouch article a while back. Well, I
might have something for you. It probably needs work, but I think it has
potential.

I'm about to finish the first game of Diplomacy I ever started, 'earth' on
USPA, with a win as Austria in 1910. Because I'm in the process of moving
across the country, I might miss the last turn or so, and I wrote my EOG
early... I just finished it.

Well, the EOG turned out to be a lot longer than I expected. Since it was a
newbie game, I wanted not only to say my farewells to the other players but
also to explain why I did what I did, and why it worked. It turned out a LOT
longer than I expected.

I have two article possibilities in mind. One is something similar to Dan
Shoham's Diplomacy Academy, with the EOGs and analysis of the game. (Too bad
that 'earth' didn't finish two months ago, or I could have been a "guest
columnist" for the Academy while Dan is away.) The other possibility is to
expand on one or two of the strategies and tactics I describe in the EOG.

If you are interested, I can forward the EOG and game history to you.

